    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLES: SPICER J400-S, W460-S - ASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>ASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>OUTPUT SHAFT</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400463">Figure 63</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400463" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400463" filename="../figg14/G1400463.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 63. Output Shaft Exploded View</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Support output shaft bearing and press output shaft into bearing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install bearing cage over bearing and secure with snap ring (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400464">Figure 64</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400464" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400464" filename="../figg14/G1400464.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 64. Install Bearing Cage Over Bearing</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install new seal into bearing cage.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install end yoke. Clean and dry threads, and coat with Loctite #680 (green) or its
                    equivalent. Install new prevailing torque nut.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten output shaft nut to 500 to 600 ft-lbs. (678 to 813 Nm).</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>If repairs to forward carrier assembly were not required, install output shaft at this
                            time.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Clean mating surfaces on axle housing and output shaft bearing retainer. Apply a 1/8
                    inch bead of Loctite 518 gasket eliminator on housing mounting flange and around bolt holes. Install
                    output shaft (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1400465">Figure 65</hotlnk>). Tighten mounting bolts evenly to 30 to 40 ft-lbs. (41
                    to 54 Nm).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1400465" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1400465" filename="../figg14/G1400465.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 65. Install Output Shaft</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install rear drive shaft.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
